nd the existing build.gradle file. Now, I need to decide if the library requires any additional setup beyond the usual scaffold to ensure meaningful coverage. Research shows that Jersey-core has provided dependencies for mail, jaxb, and osgi. So, if the scaffold only adds the library, I might need to include these dependencies to cover MIME, JAXB, and OSGi properly.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_D7V2jn1RVP4FSYZBoPijzqJ1|fc_07ec014a4b49e23b016a42b30c81e88190899cbc39a28f2c6c", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport urllib.request, os\npath=os.path.expanduser('~/jersey-core-1.14.jar')\nurllib.request.urlretrieve('https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/com/sun/jersey/jersey-core/1.14/jersey-core-1.14.jar', path)\nPY\njavap -classpath ~/jersey-core-1.14.jar -c com.sun.jersey.core.osgi.OsgiRegistry | sed -n '/getInstance/,/}/p' | head -80\nrm ~/jersey-core-1.14.jar", "timeout": 60}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2130, "output": 1196, "cacheRead": 27136, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 30462, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782756082350, "responseId": "resp_07ec014a4b49e23b016a42b2f2cd208190a249ff396f35ba4d"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_D7V2jn1RVP4FSYZBoPijzqJ1|fc_07ec014a4b49e23b016a42b30c81e88190899cbc39a28f2c6c", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Java HotSpot(TM) 64-Bit Server VM warning: Insufficient space for shared memory file:\n   1205292\nTry using the -Djava.io.tmpdir= option to select an alternate temp location.\n\n  public static synchronized com.sun.jersey.core.osgi.OsgiRegistry getInstance();\n    Code:\n         0: getstatic     #5                  // Field instance:Lcom/sun/jersey/core/osgi/OsgiRegistry;\n         3: ifnonnull     53\n         6: ldc_w         #6                  // class com/sun/jersey/core/reflection/Reflect